  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The lowest monthly temperatures on record are now plotted. Here we see the highest minimum temperatures are located around the equator where the temperature remains relatively constant with season. This is exactly what we would expect given the information about standard deviation of monthly temperature found in a previous figure. Comparing the color scale in the Congo Basin between this figure and the previous figure with maximum monthly temperatures is helpful. The red region in this figure corresponds to the blue region in the previous figure. In the figure below, we see that there are regions in the Congo where the difference between the warmest and coldest months in more than 30 years is less than 3°C! Naturally there is extremely low inter and intra-annual variability in these regions. \n",
