    "In this figure, we looked at intra-annual variability in precipitation by calculating average precipitation values for each month and calculating the standard deviation of these 12 values. By first averaging over all the years, we may underestimate the true seasonal variability if we have shifts in the timing of wet and dry seasons, as these would dampen the signal when averaging over all the years. A wet January 2000, dry February 2000 and dry January 2000, wet February 2000 would not contribute anything to the intra-annual variability although there is a difference in monthly precipitation. \n",
