    "where $P_i$ is the average precipitation [in mm] in each month, $P_{\\mathrm{annual}}$ is the average annual precipitation and \\overline{P} is the precipitation averaged over all months. \n",
    "(Taken from *Walsh and Lawler* (1981))"
