   "source": [
    "During the winter months there are divergent northeasterlies north of the equator which result in subsidence and suppressed rainfall. As the ITCZ is at its southernmost extent during this time of the year, the precipitation maxima are shifted south and the Angolan high plateau has a distinct wet season. The North African coast experiences rainfall due to increased frontal activity during this season and in fact every season apart from the summer (during which the region is dry). The precipitation in North Africa is mostly confined to the north of the Atlas Mountains in Morocco and Algeria.\n",
