    "djf_anomaly_nina.plot.contourf(ax=ax,extend='both',levels=np.arange(-1.2,1.4,0.2),cmap=\"RdYlBu_r\", transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(),cbar_kwargs={'label':'Temperature anomaly [°C]'})\n",
    "figcount=add_title(figcount,'La Ni\\u00F1a DJF composite anomalies - Temperature')\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The largest impact is found in southern Africa, As in figures {{figcount-3}} and {{figcount-4}}, we find warmer and colder temperatures there during El Niño and La Niña events, respectively.\n",
    "But also in north-western Africa and Sudan a correlation is visible.\n",
    "<span class=\"burk\">SHORT EXPLANATION WITH CIRCULATION MECHANISM -> PAPER</span>"
